-- Bug #40: multi-module `medaka run` did NOT gate on constraint / missing-impl
-- type errors.  `check` printed the real located `No impl of Display for Foo`,
-- but `run` EXECUTED the program and died on an unrelated runtime panic
-- (`E-PANIC: intToString: not an Int`), and `build` gave a THIRD message
-- (`no impl of method 'display' for type 'Foo' (slice 6)`).
--
-- Root cause: the multi-module run/build gate was `elaborateModules +
-- hadTypeErrors`, and elaborateModules sets implInferEnabled, under which
-- typecheck SKIPS checkImplObligations — the pass that raises `No impl of …`.
-- So the sticky error flag was never set.  A plain unification `Type mismatch`
-- DID set it, which is why the hole hid: probing with a mismatch shows correct
-- behaviour.  Single-file run/build were never affected (their gate is
-- analyzeLocatedG, which runs with implInferEnabled OFF) — hence the
-- single-file twin below, and the fact that this MUST stay multi-module.
--
-- ⚠️ EXIT CODE ALONE CANNOT SEE THIS BUG: `run` exited 1 either way, just for
-- the wrong reason.  The `println` below is the real assertion — if it ever
-- appears in `run`'s stdout, the ill-typed program EXECUTED.
import lib.p0_40_t.{Foo}

main : <IO> Unit
main =
  println "MUST-NOT-EXECUTE"
  println "\{Foo 1}"
